body: $DMYI It's crazy that the PIPE shares on this are locked up for 6 months after the deal closes (no shorting or anything allowed). I haven't seen that on any other deals. Bill Gates and Michael Dell both have a clause that lets them sell if shares hit $65 within 3 months of the deal closing. That's insane. With SPACs heating up
column3: and there being no selling pressure from PIPE investors at closing
column4: I think this has $QS potential around closing. (QuantumScape hit $130 right after closing.)
